<paragraph blockId="37.[151,1437,807,1480]" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,414,807,832]" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">Diagnostic characters</emphasis>
. Ovate-triangular, inequilateral shell; longer and expanded anterior side; nearly pointed posterior side; 2 divergent cardinal teeth in the right valve; 2 corresponding dorsal margin projections in the left valve. Prodissoconch: shell type ST-2A; length about 260 µm (P-1 about 110 µm); ellipsoidal outline; low convex profile; P-1 surface densely pitted; P-1/P-2 boundary rather well defined, slightly elevated; P-2 with fine concentric growth welts; transition to the nepioconch well marked.
</paragraph>
