<subSubSection pageId="37" pageNumber="38" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="37.[151,1437,807,1480]" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,308,988,1013]" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">Remarks</emphasis>
. The Leuca specimens do not fully conform with published 
<taxonomicName box="[1022,1158,988,1013]" class="Bivalvia" family="Montacutidae" genus="Kurtiella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Veneroida" pageId="37" pageNumber="38" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="tumidula">
<emphasis box="[1022,1158,988,1013]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">K. tumidula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in terms of larval shell characters. The prodissoconch of the specimens at hand is considerably (about 100 µm) smaller than that of specimens of 
<taxonomicName box="[307,440,1060,1085]" class="Bivalvia" family="Montacutidae" genus="Kurtiella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Veneroida" pageId="37" pageNumber="38" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="tumidula">
<emphasis box="[307,440,1060,1085]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">K. tumidula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as measured by some authors (e.g. 
<bibRefCitation author="Gofas" box="[846,1076,1060,1085]" pageId="37" pageNumber="38" refString="Gofas, S. &amp; Salas, C. (2008) A review of European ' Mysella ' species (Bivalvia: Montacutidae), with description of Kurtiella new genus. Journal of Molluscan Studies, 74, 119 - 135. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1093 / mollus / eym 053" type="journal article" year="2008">Gofas &amp; Salas 2008</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Oliver" box="[1089,1295,1060,1085]" pageId="37" pageNumber="38" refString="Oliver, P. G., Holmes, A. M., Killeen, I. J. &amp; Turner, J. A. (2016) Marine Bivalve Shells of the British Isles (Mollusca: Bivalvia). Amgueddfa Cymru-National Museum Wales. Available from: http: // naturalhistory. museumwales. ac. uk / britishbivalves. (Accessed 25 August 2016)" type="journal article" year="2016">
Oliver 
<emphasis box="[1169,1226,1060,1085]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">et al.</emphasis>
2016
</bibRefCitation>
). Otherwise, prodissoconch shape and P-1 dimensions are comparable. P-2 size difference could overstep mere species variability, so we prefer not to assign our specimens to 
<taxonomicName box="[769,901,1132,1157]" class="Bivalvia" family="Montacutidae" genus="Kurtiella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Veneroida" pageId="37" pageNumber="38" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="tumidula">
<emphasis box="[769,901,1132,1157]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">K. tumidula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="37.[151,1437,807,1480]" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,339,1167,1192]" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">Occurrence</emphasis>
. Box-corer samples BC04 (1 specimen), BC11 (3), BC67 (2); cores BC04 (1), BC05 (5), BC21 (12), BC51 (8), BC67 (2), BC72 (21). Maximum length: 
<quantity box="[791,881,1204,1229]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.5" pageId="37" pageNumber="38" unit="mm" value="2.5">2.5 mm</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="37" pageNumber="38" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="37.[151,1437,807,1480]" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,490,1239,1264]" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">Distribution and habitat</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName box="[505,714,1239,1264]" class="Bivalvia" family="Montacutidae" genus="Kurtiella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Veneroida" pageId="37" pageNumber="38" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="tumidula">
<emphasis box="[505,714,1239,1264]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">Kurtiella tumidula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was hitherto known to live from 
<collectingCountry box="[1091,1181,1240,1264]" name="Norway" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">Norway</collectingCountry>
to North America, the 
<collectingRegion box="[151,233,1276,1300]" country="Portugal" name="Acores" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">Azores</collectingRegion>
, the Strait of 
<collectingCountry box="[390,491,1276,1301]" name="Gibraltar" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">Gibraltar</collectingCountry>
and the Mediterranean entrance; past Mediterranean records referred only to worn empty shells of probable Pleistocene age (
<bibRefCitation author="Dautzenberg" box="[643,858,1311,1336]" pageId="37" pageNumber="38" refString="Dautzenberg, P. (1889) Contribution a la faune malacologique des Iles Acores. Resultats des Campagnes Scientifiques du Prince de Monaco, I, 1 - 112. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 13198" type="book chapter" year="1889">Dautzenberg 1889</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Verrill" box="[873,1114,1311,1336]" pageId="37" pageNumber="38" refString="Verrill, A. E. &amp; Bush, K. J. (1898) Revision of the deep-water Mollusca of the Atlantic coast of North America, with descriptions of new genera and species. Part I. - Bivalvia. Proceedings U. S. National Museum, 20 (1139), 775 - 901. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.5479 / si. 00963801.20 - 1139.775" type="journal article" year="1898">Verrill &amp; Bush 1898</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Gofas" box="[1130,1371,1311,1336]" pageId="37" pageNumber="38" refString="Gofas, S. &amp; Salas, C. (2008) A review of European ' Mysella ' species (Bivalvia: Montacutidae), with description of Kurtiella new genus. Journal of Molluscan Studies, 74, 119 - 135. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1093 / mollus / eym 053" type="journal article" year="2008">Gofas &amp; Salas 2008</bibRefCitation>
). The present record (if confirmed) could therefore be the first Recent one for the species in the Mediterranean, even if no live specimens were recovered. 
<taxonomicName box="[510,718,1383,1408]" class="Bivalvia" family="Montacutidae" genus="Kurtiella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Veneroida" pageId="37" pageNumber="38" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="tumidula">
<emphasis box="[510,718,1383,1408]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">Kurtiella tumidula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a commensal element (host unknown) dwelling on mud from the shelf edge to about 
<quantity box="[411,496,1420,1444]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.0" pageId="37" pageNumber="38" unit="m" value="2000.0">2000 m</quantity>
depth (
<bibRefCitation author="Jeffreys" box="[580,736,1420,1445]" pageId="37" pageNumber="38" refString="Jeffreys, J. G. (1866) Report on dredging among the Hebrides. The Annals and Magazine of Natural History, 3 (18), 387 - 397." type="journal article" year="1866">Jeffreys 1866</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Nordsieck" box="[748,929,1420,1445]" pageId="37" pageNumber="38" refString="Nordsieck, F. (1969) Die europaischen Meeresmuscheln (Bivalvia) vom Eismeer bis Kapverden, Mittelmeer und Schwarzes Meer. Gustav Fischer Verlag, Stuttgart, XIII + 256 pp." type="book" year="1969">Nordsieck 1969</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Gofas" box="[940,1168,1420,1445]" pageId="37" pageNumber="38" refString="Gofas, S. &amp; Salas, C. (2008) A review of European ' Mysella ' species (Bivalvia: Montacutidae), with description of Kurtiella new genus. Journal of Molluscan Studies, 74, 119 - 135. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1093 / mollus / eym 053" type="journal article" year="2008">Gofas &amp; Salas 2008</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Oliver" box="[1180,1382,1420,1445]" pageId="37" pageNumber="38" refString="Oliver, P. G., Holmes, A. M., Killeen, I. J. &amp; Turner, J. A. (2016) Marine Bivalve Shells of the British Isles (Mollusca: Bivalvia). Amgueddfa Cymru-National Museum Wales. Available from: http: // naturalhistory. museumwales. ac. uk / britishbivalves. (Accessed 25 August 2016)" type="journal article" year="2016">
Oliver 
<emphasis box="[1258,1315,1420,1445]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">et al.</emphasis>
2016
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="37.[151,1437,807,1480]" box="[199,1007,1455,1480]" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,360,1455,1480]" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">Fossil record.</emphasis>
Pleistocene? of the Mediterranean (
<bibRefCitation author="Gofas" box="[764,995,1455,1480]" pageId="37" pageNumber="38" refString="Gofas, S. &amp; Salas, C. (2008) A review of European ' Mysella ' species (Bivalvia: Montacutidae), with description of Kurtiella new genus. Journal of Molluscan Studies, 74, 119 - 135. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1093 / mollus / eym 053" type="journal article" year="2008">Gofas &amp; Salas 2008</bibRefCitation>
